#X text 36 134 Hence \, the distinction between them is somewhat silly today and points to a historical divide \, since FM synthesis and filtering are not mutually exclusive. Especially in Pd \, nothing stops you from combining these principles or any synthesis techniques and effects. In the example below we have a cross modulation and a [decay~] envelope that controls both a PM index and a filter modulation. Both do shape the sound. Moreover \, we randomly rotate both outputs of the cross modulation., f 65;
#X text 36 12 The DX7 did not include filters and departed from the traditional analog-subtractive approach \, where harmonically rich oscillators are shaped by filter modulation. Instead \, the DX7's tone is created and shaped directly through FM synthesis \, where sounds that resemble filter sweeps are usually the result of changes in FM parameters rather than actual filtering. Later digital synthesizers \, including some FM-based instruments \, eventually incorporated filters alongside FM synthesis., f 65;
